people don't need to do

05:03.477 --> 05:05.609
that over-the-top,
crazy stuff.
[gasps]

05:05.653 --> 05:08.090
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

05:08.133 --> 05:09.439
Daddy, is this for me?Yes.

05:09.483 --> 05:13.008
♪ My Bonnie lies
over the ocean ♪

05:13.051 --> 05:17.795
♪ My Bonnie lies
over the sea... ♪

05:17.839 --> 05:19.014
What the hell is this?

05:19.057 --> 05:23.235
Oh, there's Cliff
and Betty. June!

05:23.279 --> 05:25.281
Bonnie, I know we've missed
a lot of big events together

05:25.325 --> 05:26.717
while we were working,
so I decided to gather

05:26.761 --> 05:28.763
our best friends and our family

05:28.806 --> 05:30.025
to show you just how much

05:30.068 --> 05:32.375
your life and your love
means to me.

05:32.419 --> 05:35.683
BOTH: ♪ My Bonnie lies
over the ocean ♪

05:35.726 --> 05:40.252
♪ 'Cause there's only one
Bonnie for me. ♪

05:44.169 --> 05:46.302
[squeals]

05:46.346 --> 05:47.695
Oh, I was wrong, Claire.

05:47.738 --> 05:50.045
This is what true love is.

05:55.877 --> 05:57.792
[sighs]

05:57.835 --> 05:59.794
Claire-bear, we're good, right?

05:59.837 --> 06:00.882
Our fire's still burning?

06:00.925 --> 06:03.363
Yeah, of course it is.

06:06.409 --> 06:08.759
No, I mean, when Cooper
does a grand gesture,

06:08.803 --> 06:10.152
it's one thing,
but now your parents?

06:10.195 --> 06:12.807
No, babe, we are en fuego.

06:12.850 --> 06:14.635
Okay?

06:14.678 --> 06:16.898
We just need to accept
that our fire

06:16.941 --> 06:20.815
is more of a controlled burn.

06:20.858 --> 06:23.034
I guess that sounds good.

06:23.078 --> 06:25.385
