13:41.951 --> 13:44.127
Yeah, badass.

13:44.171 --> 13:47.130
I heard guys like us can't be
buried in a Jewish cemetery.

13:47.174 --> 13:49.306
No, I'm saying that looks nasty.

13:49.350 --> 13:52.657
I'm a dirty dog,
through and through.

13:52.701 --> 13:54.790
Sir, I'm trying to tell you

13:54.834 --> 13:57.880
your tattoo
is horribly infected.

13:57.924 --> 14:01.318
So that's not just muscle juice
leaking out of it?

14:10.066 --> 14:10.545
[wincing]

14:10.588 --> 14:12.025
Stop.

14:12.068 --> 14:14.592
Jake, I-I'm not trying
to scare you,

14:14.636 --> 14:16.159
but this looks very serious.

14:16.203 --> 14:18.118
That infection
is verging on necrosis.

14:18.161 --> 14:19.380
I'm sorry, I just don't see

14:19.423 --> 14:20.860
a world where
we're not amputating.

14:20.903 --> 14:23.166
[high-pitched]:
No-- put it down!
What are you doing?!

14:23.210 --> 14:24.907
Hey, hey! What's going on?

14:24.951 --> 14:28.432
[both laugh]Oh, my God.

14:28.476 --> 14:32.349
Your face. Your face.

14:32.393 --> 14:35.657
[imitating yelps]

14:35.700 --> 14:37.702
It's for the lime, Jake.

14:39.617 --> 14:41.968
BONNIE: Oh, my God.Don't worry, buddy.

14:42.011 --> 14:43.186
We're just gonna give you
this antibiotic

14:43.230 --> 14:45.101
and it should clear it up
in a week or so.

14:45.145 --> 14:48.757
But I have to ask, Jake, why on
Earth would you get a tattoo?

14:48.800 --> 14:50.237
Well, because I thought
only new couples

14:50.280 --> 14:52.152
had to do these grand gestures.

14:52.195 --> 14:53.762
But then, you two
started doing them.

14:53.805 --> 14:55.590
Well, technically,
only Gerald did one.

14:55.633 --> 14:58.854
Oh, I repaid the favor.
Nothing's for free, Jake.

14:58.898 --> 15:01.291
[chuckles]

15:04.860 --> 15:08.168
[retches]

15:08.211 --> 15:10.126
All right, I guess I should
probably sterilize this,

15:10.170 --> 15:11.562
being-- all right,

15:11.606 --> 15:14.174
there we go.

15:14.217 --> 15:16.089
Other arm, other arm, please.

15:16.132 --> 15:18.134
Other arm.All right, very well.

15:18.178 --> 15:20.223
Could you give me
a countdown, please?

15:20.267 --> 15:23.052
Oh, I wish I could,
but I'm not a pediatrician.

15:23.096 --> 15:24.967
All right, don't
be surprised

15:25.011 --> 15:26.664
if the antibiotics make
your arm a little sore.

15:26.708 --> 15:28.928
And keep washing that area,
or we'll have to, you know...

15:28.971 --> 15:30.103
[screams]

15:30.146 --> 15:31.974
[both laugh]

15:32.018 --> 15:33.758
Bonnie, Bonnie.

15:33.802 --> 15:35.586
He fell for it again.

15:38.198 --> 15:39.286
Hey, Claire, you home?

15:39.329 --> 15:40.896
Jake. Where have you been?

15:40.940 --> 15:42.811
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

15:42.854 --> 15:44.204
Uh, I-I...

15:44.247 --> 15:46.510
Got a little infection
going on in my tat.
What?

15:46.554 --> 15:49.339
Yeah, my arms are so sore,
I can barely move them both.

15:49.383 --> 15:51.385
Man, this is awful timing.
Well, I'm not supposed to say,

15:51.428 --> 15:53.387
but Claire's planned
an awesome surprise for you.

15:53.430 --> 15:54.475
Really? What is it?

15:54.518 --> 15:56.346
Check your phone.

15:56.390 --> 15:58.131
[grunting]:
Okay.

15:58.174 --> 16:02.004
"Dr. Dunk," that's me,

16:02.048 --> 16:05.268
"Grab your keys and make
a fast break to Henley Park

16:05.312 --> 16:06.617
or you'll be
called for a foul."

16:06.661 --> 16:08.054
This is basketball-related?

16:08.097 --> 16:09.925
Yeah. All I can say is that
Claire's really excited

16:09.969 --> 16:11.274
to do this grand gesture
for you.

16:11.318 --> 16:13.929
Ah, nice. I mean,
I can't play basketball,

16:13.973 --> 16:15.931
but I might as well
drive down there and thank her.

16:15.975 --> 16:18.325
Grab my keys, man.
Let's go. [chuckles]

16:18.368 --> 16:20.370
Ha, ha.

16:24.461 --> 16:27.464
You know what? You know what--
you steer, I'll do the pedals.

16:30.641 --> 16:32.600
CLAIRE:
Jake!

16:32.643 --> 16:34.689
Oh, I'm so glad
you're here. What...

16:34.732 --> 16:37.257
Why are you walking
like you've been lassoed?

16:38.519 --> 16:41.087
Can I talk to you for a second
over here, please?

16:41.130 --> 16:42.697
Over here...

16:42.740 --> 16:45.874
Yeah?Yeah, uh, listen, um,

16:45.917 --> 16:49.486
I love that you planned this
grand gesture for me, but, um...

16:49.530 --> 16:51.619
My champ stamp
got infected, and, uh,

16:51.662 --> 16:54.709
I can't play
basketball today.

16:54.752 --> 16:56.058
Seriously?

16:56.102 --> 16:58.408
Yeah.
[sighs]
That stinks.

16:58.452 --> 17:01.672
Well, you know how you've always
wanted to play with NBA players?

17:01.716 --> 17:03.326
Yes.

17:03.370 --> 17:07.287
I kind of got you into a charity
tournament with your favorite.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.333
It's Ben Simmons.

17:11.856 --> 17:14.772
[squeaking]:
What? He's-- aww, come on.

17:14.816 --> 17:17.949
What? Is it...?
How did you do this?

17:17.993 --> 17:19.168
Uh, Cooper knows him.

17:19.212 --> 17:20.865
Yeah, I didn't even know
Ben played basketball.

17:20.909 --> 17:22.867
But if he's as good at this game
as he is at Scrabble,

17:22.911 --> 17:24.086
you're gonna be in great shape.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.653
[groans]

17:25.696 --> 17:27.263
Hey, Coop.

17:27.307 --> 17:29.135
Hey, man.
Hey, Claire.

17:29.178 --> 17:31.398
What's up?
What's up, Ben Simmons?

17:32.877 --> 17:35.184
So, um, anyway, um,
I'm so sorry, Ben,

17:35.228 --> 17:36.403
but I think we're gonna
have to take a rain check,

17:36.446 --> 17:38.361
'cause my husband's
in pretty serious...

17:38.405 --> 17:40.450
Awe of his amazing wife.

17:40.494 --> 17:42.061
We doing this, man.

17:42.104 --> 17:44.150
We gonna do this.

17:44.193 --> 17:45.368
CLAIRE:
Okay, you got this, babe!

17:45.412 --> 17:48.980
All right, guys,
let's have some fun.

17:49.024 --> 17:52.158
♪ Lonely bird, broken wings,
but I still fly ♪

17:52.201 --> 17:54.377
♪ Ooh, change up,
hunger never came up ♪

17:54.421 --> 17:57.337
♪ From Oakland out to Philly,
it's the same love ♪

17:57.380 --> 17:58.773
[audience cheering]

17:58.816 --> 18:01.080
♪ They got to call me Mr. T...

18:01.123 --> 18:03.473
It's all good. Just
getting used to the speed.

18:03.517 --> 18:05.214
♪ Chasing history,
20 years from now ♪

18:05.258 --> 18:06.955
♪ The generation
will still mention me ♪

18:08.348 --> 18:10.524
Oh...♪ We play to win

18:10.567 --> 18:12.787
♪ Making sure I don't say this
all again... ♪

18:12.830 --> 18:15.137
I thought you played
college ball.

18:15.181 --> 18:17.270
That was a pass, bro.

18:17.313 --> 18:19.533
Well, I, uh, really thought
that Jake was gonna be able

18:19.576 --> 18:21.100
to play without his arms,
but it turns out,

18:21.143 --> 18:23.754
I didn't know
what basketball was.

18:25.539 --> 18:28.585
Hey. I love you, babe.
You got this.

18:30.587 --> 18:32.589
All right, Ben, let's huddle up.

18:32.633 --> 18:35.157
Do we have to? Your shoulder
smells like really old turkey.

18:35.201 --> 18:36.332
Listen, I got an idea.

18:36.376 --> 18:37.551
We're gonna win this game
with some

18:37.594 --> 18:39.596
good old-fashioned fundamentals.

18:41.381 --> 18:43.426
[audience cheering]

18:44.949 --> 18:46.386
Go with what you know, bro.

18:47.517 --> 18:49.476
[cheering]

18:55.308 --> 18:57.614
[screams]

19:04.969 --> 19:06.971
[sighs] Today was
so amazing, Claire-Bear.

19:07.015 --> 19:09.017
Yeah? Oh...[grunts]

19:12.629 --> 19:14.544
Get your butt in here for a hug.

19:14.588 --> 19:16.938
Oh...[shouts]

19:16.981 --> 19:18.635
Do it... Oh!

19:18.679 --> 19:20.594
Okay. [chuckles]
Right?

19:20.637 --> 19:22.596
Worked out well. Yeah.Uh-- pleasure doing
business with you. Yeah.

19:22.639 --> 19:24.685
Yes, yes.

19:24.728 --> 19:27.862
Ah, I'm gonna have to think of
something huge to top this.

19:27.905 --> 19:30.821
Uh, is it crazy that I don't
want another grand gesture?

19:30.865 --> 19:33.476
I mean, they're sweet and all,
but I kind of prefer

19:33.520 --> 19:34.782
when you just do little things,

19:34.825 --> 19:37.350
like, how you always fill up
my car with gas.

19:37.393 --> 19:39.569
Or those cute little notes
you always leave me.Yeah.

19:39.613 --> 19:40.831
Or like how you always
bring an extra spoon

19:40.875 --> 19:42.050
whenever you eat ice cream.

19:42.093 --> 19:43.269
Yeah, exactly.

19:43.312 --> 19:45.445
They're more like
bland gestures, but...

19:45.488 --> 19:46.837
Mm....they're better.

19:46.881 --> 19:48.056
Because that means
that we're thinking

19:48.099 --> 19:49.884
about each other all the time.

19:49.927 --> 19:51.755
Totally. Like,
I'm with you right now,

19:51.799 --> 19:53.192
but I still miss you
whenever I blink.

19:53.235 --> 19:54.541
Claire, where'd you...

19:54.584 --> 19:56.282
Oh, my God, Claire, I can't...

19:56.325 --> 19:57.718
Claire, where'd you--
oh, there you are.

19:57.761 --> 19:59.328
[laughs]Oh, my God.

19:59.372 --> 20:01.461
You guys are geniuses.

20:01.504 --> 20:03.289
We're listening.Go on.

20:03.332 --> 20:05.421
I kept trying to surprise
Vanessa with a big move,

20:05.465 --> 20:06.770
but none of them
were having an impact.

20:06.814 --> 20:08.685
So I thought, "What would
Jake and Claire do?"

20:08.729 --> 20:11.732
And I filled up her gas tank and
she went absolutely nuts for it.

20:11.775 --> 20:14.082
Oh, my God.
Well, that's amazing.

20:14.125 --> 20:16.476
Yeah, I know. And I got to say,
I'm-I'm really grateful

20:16.519 --> 20:18.956
for you guys
letting me stay here.

20:19.000 --> 20:20.567
You're really onto something
with this normal life.

20:20.610 --> 20:21.829
[Jake and Claire chuckle]

20:23.178 --> 20:25.920
Well, uh, we're happy
to have you here, Coops.

20:25.963 --> 20:27.530
And, uh, take it from us:

20:27.574 --> 20:30.185
sometimes $40 of gas
is all it takes.

20:30.229 --> 20:33.580
$40? I'm gonna need the number
of your jet fuel guy.

20:35.277 --> 20:36.800
Oh.Oh, you filled up her plane?

20:36.844 --> 20:39.977
Yeah.Different situation.

20:40.021 --> 20:41.892
Yeah, she said fueling up
her private jet

20:41.936 --> 20:44.025
was the most thoughtful thing
anyone's ever done for her.

20:44.068 --> 20:46.767
Thanks. $40, ha...

20:46.810 --> 20:47.855
Oh.
Ah.

20:47.898 --> 20:49.900
[phone buzzing]

20:49.944 --> 20:51.380
Cooper's phone.

20:51.424 --> 20:52.729
Uh...[clattering]

20:52.773 --> 20:55.384
Oh-- oh, my God. It's The Rock.

20:55.428 --> 20:56.342
Oh, my God. Are you serious?

